snippet: MoMA has purchased important works from the 1960s and ’70s by the feminist artists Valie Export and Martha Rosler.
abstract: Carol Vogel Inside Art column; the Museum of Modern Art acquires works by Martha Rosler and Valie Export from the 1960s and 1970s; National Gallery of Art acquires the painting Still Life With Fruit and Nuts by Robert Seldon Duncanson; Maurizio Cattelan plans to open a small gallery in Chelsea called Family Business.
lead_paragraph: MoMA has purchased important works from the 1960s and ’70s by the feminist artists Valie Export and Martha Rosler.

headline.seo: MoMA Acquires Works by Valie Export and Martha Rosler
headline.main: MoMA Acquires Works by Feminist Artists
